    "In [10], On the other hand, the authors propose a framework that groups 34 metrics into 5 dimensions: (1) functional requirements, ensuring the method's core capabilities are met; (2) operational requirements, detailing practical implementation needs; (3) usability criteria, evaluating user experience and effectiveness; (4) security and privacy considerations, identifying potential vulnerabilities; and (5) validation methods, confirming the method's reliability through testing.",
    "These dimensions provide a comprehensive framework for evaluating and comparing explainability methods, ensuring thorough understanding and standardisation in the field.",
